description:
This character actively learns a foreign language to, for example, be able to communicate with his girlfriend in her native language.

The trait can be used for a character learning: 
- [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modern_language]Living Language[/url] ​​(such as [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_language]French[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_language]German[/url] or [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_language]English[/url]);
- [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extinct_language]Dead Languages[/url] ​​(such as [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin]Latin[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burgundians#Language]Burgundian[/url] or [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Norse]Old Norse[/url]);
- [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constructed_language]Constructed Languages[/url] ​​(such as [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esperanto]Esperanto[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lingua_Franca_Nova]Lingua Franca Nova[/url] or [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interlingue_language]Interlingue language[/url]);
- [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fictional_language]Fictional Languages[/url] ​​(such as [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dothraki_language]Dothraki[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khuzdul]Khuzdul[/url] or [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quenya]Quenya[/url]).
- [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macaronic_language]Macaronic Language[/url] although this one is for a comic element (such as [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Franglais]Franglais[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Engrish]Engrish[/url] or Franponais).
